# This project uses Gaia — at-hand reference

Full contract: `AGENTS.md` → *About Gaia*. See also
`docs/HOW_TO_PROMOTE.md` in the Gaia repo.

Seeded from **Gaia** (https://github.com/frankpietro/gaia). `.gaia/manifest.json` records
the exact Gaia commit this project is on.

## Pull from Gaia

The sessionStart hook injects a freshness note into your opening
context if this project is behind upstream. You can also run:

```bash
gaia check        # fast, local: is this project behind?
gaia whatsnew     # what changed in core/ and reference/
gaia update       # re-seed; preserves local edits; never touches docs/
gaia sync         # fetch + ff-only pull inside $GAIA_HOME
```

**"Behind" protocol**: reconcile conflicts against
`docs/knowledge.md` first (project-local decisions win, record the
override), then `gaia update`, then ship a dedicated
`chore(gaia): bump to <short-sha>` PR.

## Push to Gaia — outbox only, never from this chat

**Never open a PR against Gaia from this session.** Upstream
promotions run in a dedicated Cursor chat opened against the Gaia
repo. From here, *stage* the proposal:

1. Add the learning to `docs/knowledge.md` with a `GENERAL:` prefix.
2. Queue it in the outbox:

   ```bash
   gaia outbox add \
     --tier core \
     --target core/AGENTS.md \
     --title "<short headline>" \
     --body "Why + what to change + links"
   ```

   Tiers: `core` (universal rule), `reference` (preference or
   archetype tweak), `archetype:<name>` (specific archetype).
3. Commit `.gaia/outbox.md` with the rest of the PR. Mention it in
   the PR body so the user knows to drain soon.

## Where knowledge belongs

| Scope | Where it goes |
|---|---|
| Specific to *this* project only | `docs/knowledge.md` |
| Any Gaia-seeded project would benefit | `docs/knowledge.md` with `GENERAL:` + outbox entry |
| Named, reusable technical recipe | `docs/knowledge.md` + outbox entry, target `reference/patterns/<slug>.md` |

When in doubt, start in `docs/knowledge.md`. If the same learning
appears a second time in a different project, queue it.

## Patterns — consult before inventing

Before tackling cross-cutting concerns (CI setup, migrations,
secret rotation, feature flags, logging, Dockerfile, release):

```bash
ls .gaia/reference/patterns/
```

If a filename matches, read it before reinventing. A recipe needed
twice across projects → queue a `reference`-tier outbox entry
proposing a new pattern file.

## Never edit

- `.gaia/manifest.json` — managed by `gaia update`.
- `.gaia/reference/` — seeded Tier-2 snapshot; change upstream via
  the outbox.
